ğŸ‘€ visual:

<visual>
  <geometry>
    <box size="3 0.1 1"/>
  </geometry>
  <material name="white">
    <color rgba="1 1 1 1"/>
  </material>
</visual>

This controls how the object looks, but doesnâ€™t affect physics.
	â€¢	geometry says what shape it is: box, sphere, mesh, etc.
	â€¢	box size="3 0.1 1" is:
	â€¢	Width (X) = 3 units
	â€¢	Depth (Y) = 0.1 units (thin)
	â€¢	Height (Z) = 1 unit
	â€¢	color rgba="1 1 1 1" = white (1,1,1) and fully opaque (alpha = 1)

ğŸ¨ You can change color to something like:

